data.description: Captivating views of the calm waters of the inner harbor can be yours every night in this gorgeous home! Spacious rooms, soaring ceilings, abundant windows and storage make this home so welcoming. Launch your boat or other watercraft from your own dock. Details make a difference in a home of this caliber with beautiful hardwood floors throughout most of the main floor. Gather with friends and family in the expansive great room featuring wood beams across the cathedral ceiling, built-in cabinetry, towering windows and a stone fireplace with gas logs. The well-appointed kitchen has many fine features including a pot filler, double ovens, and a breakfast bar. Butler's pantry can double as a beverage bar which makes it so perfect for entertaining. Take time to indulge yourself in the first floor Master Suite with its roomy tile shower and double vanity. Plenty of options for your overnight guests with one guestroom on the main floor and two more generously-sized guestrooms upstairs. There is also a powder room for guests on the main floor. The laundry room is highest quality with generous granite counters and storage cabinets. Outdoor entertaining is a breeze on the composite back deck overlooking the dock and waterfront. Drive your cars plus a golf cart or other wheeled toys into the 2 & 1/2 car garage. Neighborhood amenities include 18-hole golf course, The Pointe restaurant, two marinas, tennis and pickleball courts, community center, dog park, boat ramp, kayak launch, walking trails, picnic pavilion, and playground. All this and it is located just minutes from all the shopping and restaurants in historic downtown New Bern.
